visualization :\par
\b0\fs28 Visualization plays a crucial role in understanding and communicating earthquake prediction models and their results. Here are some common visualization techniques used in earthquake prediction:\par
\par
Seismic Activity Heatmaps:\par
\par
Heatmaps can show the density of earthquakes over a specific area. They can be used to identify regions with high seismic activity and potential earthquake hotspots.\par
Time Series Plots:\par
\par
Time series plots can show the historical seismic activity in a region. They can help identify patterns and trends over time.\par
Seismic Event Maps:\par
\par
Visualize the location and magnitude of recent seismic events on a map. Different colors or sizes of data points can represent the magnitude of the earthquakes.\par
